{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-8219"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Community Office Support Services Operations"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "8219"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :commercial/office-support-services
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:data-privacy :local-jobs :access-to-services]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :office-support-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :labor]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:optimization]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "OfficeSupport-LLM ⊣ Office Support Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph
 (langgraph.graph, ofsup.operation/build), append-only audit ledger
 (ofsup.store/ledger + append-ledger!, MemStore and a DatomicStore
 backed by langchain.db via langchain-store.core). A back-office
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for office-support services
 (photocopying/document-preparation/mailing) -- not the authority that
 finalizes a data-privacy-compliance decision over a client's
 documents and not the authority that releases/discloses a client's
 documents (both remain a certified operator's own act). Four ops
 (`:log-service-record` / `:schedule-service-operation` / `:flag-
 confidentiality-concern` / `:coordinate-supply-order`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Ten HARD invariants (effect-not-propose, op/action
 allowlist x2, scope-exclusion text-scan, no-spec-basis, record-not-
 verified, registration-unconfirmed, open-confidentiality-concern,
 already-scheduled, already-coordinating) elaborate this blueprint's
 Governor, grounded in a per-jurisdiction spec-basis catalog
 (`ofsup.facts`) citing REAL public sources (California Legal Document
 Assistants Act Bus. & Prof. Code SS6400, UK ICO data-protection-fee
 notification, Japan APPI/PPC) -- never a fabricated jurisdiction
 requirement. `:flag-confidentiality-concern` ALWAYS escalates to a
 human office-support operations coordinator via the compiled graph's
 `:request-approval` node (`interrupt-before`, checkpoint-based
 resume), independently enforced by both `ofsup.phase` (never in any
 phase's `:auto` set) and `ofsup.governor` (unconditional `high-
 stakes`); `:log-service-record` / `:schedule-service-operation` /
 low-cost `:coordinate-supply-order` are phase-3 auto-eligible when
 the Governor is clean. Every commit/hold/approval-rejected decision
 lands in the append-only ledger -- 47 tests / 446 assertions green
 (`clojure -M:dev:test`, including a StateGraph integration test
 exercising commit / hard-hold / escalate-approve / escalate-reject
 end to end via `langgraph.graph/run*`), demo runnable end-to-end
 (`clojure -M:dev:run`)."}
